---

Halve the @sugar snap peas{80%g}.

Trim and peel the @carrot{1}(peeled). Use the #peeler{} to peel long ribbons down the
length of the carrot, stopping at the core.

Peel and grate the @garlic{2%cloves}(peeled and grated) (or use a #garlic press{}).

Heat a large #frying pan{} on medium-high heat (no oil).

Once hot, add the @British pork mince{240%g} and cook until browned, ~{5-6%minutes}.
Use a #spoon{} to break it up as it cooks, then drain and discard any excess fat.
Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw mince. The pork is
> cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

While the pork browns, bring a large #saucepan{} of water to the boil with @salt{1/4%tsp}.

When boiling, add the @egg noodle nests{2} to the water and bring back to the boil.
Cook until tender, ~{4%minutes}.

Once cooked, drain in a #colander{}.

> TIP: Run the noodles under cold water to stop them sticking together.

Once the pork has browned, add the sugar snaps, @red Thai style paste{50%g} and garlic
to the pan. Stir-fry until fragrant, ~{1%minute}.

Add the cooked noodles, carrot ribbons, @ketjap manis{50%ml}, @water{50%ml} and
@sugar{1/2%tsp} to the pan. Stir together until well combined and piping hot,
then remove from the heat. Taste and season with @salt{} and @pepper{} if needed.

When ready, share the pork noodles between your #bowls{}.

Sprinkle over the @white sesame seeds{5%g} to finish. Enjoy!